<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Flywheel and Flywheel Housing -
        Installation - Rear Oil Seal
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="6">
        <title>Rear Oil Seal</title>
        <figure id="f2651321.5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH07/H07030.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Applying sealant to the crankshaft and seal assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a 360&#176; bead of Loctite&#174; hydraulic sealant to the crankshaft where the rear
                oil seal assembly will be positioned.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651322" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH07/H07009.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the rear oil seal installer base</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install base component of oil seal installer onto crankshaft and tighten bolts (2).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651322.5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH07/H07031.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Applying sealant to the seal assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a 360&#176; bead of Loctite&#174; hydraulic sealant to the outside diameter of the
                rear oil seal assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651323" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH07/H07012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Placing oil seal onto rear oil seal installer base</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Orient steel face of oil seal outward (towards transmission) and start seal onto oil seal
                installer base.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651324" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH07/H07011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing rear oil seal installer onto base</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place oil seal installer up to steel face of seal and gently push by hand into flywheel
                housing as far as possible.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651325" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH07/H07010.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the rear oil seal</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put washer and forcing nut onto shaft and tighten until rear oil seal bottoms out in
                flywheel housing. The seal will be placed at the correct location (depth).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
